It was Cricket South Africa (CSA) former president Mtutuzeli Nyoka who said last week “the house is on fire”. But, to use Nyoka’s metaphor, current president Chris Nenzani, as the householder, stood around and did nothing – maybe even passed the cans of petrol tossed onto the blaze – and let someone else summon the fire brigade. So, as the outgoing SA Cricketers’ Association chief executive, Tony Irish, correctly observed, it was appalling that Nenzani and the rest of the tainted and compromised board of directors of CSA did not resign. Instead, they heaped all the blame on CSA’s suspended...